recall(s): [{u'NHTSACampaignNumber': u'19V684000', u'Conequence': u'The lack of an image in the back-up camera display increases the risk of a crash.', u'Notes': u'Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.', u'Component': u'BACK OVER PREVENTION: SENSING SYSTEM: CAMERA', u'Summary': u'BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2018 540d, 2018-2020 530i, 530i xDrive, 540i, 540i xDrive, M550i xDrive, M5, 530e, 530e xDrive, X3 sDrive, X3 xDrive, X3 M40i, X3 M, and 2019-2020 X4 xDrive, X4 M40i, X4 M, X7 xDrive, X7 M50i, 740Li, 740Li xDrive, 750Li, 750Li xDrive, 8 Series Convertible and Coupe 840i, 840i xDrive, M850i xDrive, X5 sDrive, X5 xDrive, X5 M50i, X6 xDrive, X6 M50i, 330i, 330i xDrive, M340i, M340i xDrive, Z4 sDrive, Z4 M40i, 740Le xDrive and 745Le xDrive, 2018-2019 640i xDrive Gran Turismo and Rolls-Royce Phantom, 2019 M850i xDrive Gran Coupe and Rolls-Royce Cullinan and 2020 Toyota Supra vehicles.  \r\n\r\nThe back-up camera and display settings can be adjusted such that the rear view image is no longer visible and the system will retain that setting the next time the vehicle is placed in reverse. The recall began August 21, 2019.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417. ', u'ModelYear': u'2020', u'Model': u'X5', u'Make': u'BMW', u'ReportReceivedDate': u'/Date(1566964800000-0400)/', u'Manufacturer': u'BMW of North America, LLC'}]

[{u'NHTSACampaignNumber': u'19V667000', u'Conequence': u'A fuel leak in the presence of the ignition source can increase the risk of a fire.', u'Notes': u'Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.', u'Component': u'FUEL SYSTEM, GASOLINE:STORAGE:TANK ASSEMBLY', u'Summary': u'General Motors LLC (GM) is recalling certain 2019-2020 Chevrolet Equinox all-wheel drive vehicles. [{u'NHTSACampaignNumber': u'19V761000', u'Conequence': u'Unintended activation of the driveline-protection system will cause unintended braking on the wheel on the opposite side of the failed sensor, causing the vehicle to pull to one side unexpectedly, increasing the risk of a crash.', u'Notes': u'Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.', u'Component': u'ELECTRONIC STABILITY CONTROL | SERVICE BRAKES | SERVICE BRAKES, HYDRAULIC:ANTILOCK:WHEEL SPEED SENSOR', u'Summary': u'General Motors LLC (GM) is recalling certain 2015-2020 Chevrolet Suburban, Tahoe, and GMC Yukon, and 2014-2018 Chevrolet Silverado 1500 and GMC Sierra 1500 vehicles equipped with a 5.3-liter engine, a 3.08-ratio rear axle and four-wheel drive. [{u'NHTSACampaignNumber': u'19V633000', u'Conequence': u'A seat back with an improperly assembled recliner mechanism may have reduced strength and may not adequately restrain an occupant in a crash, increasing the risk of injury.', u'Notes': u'Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.', u'Component': u'SEATS:FRONT ASSEMBLY:RECLINER | SEATS:MID/REAR ASSEMBLY', u'Summary': u'Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2018-2020 F-150 and 2019-2020 F-250, F-350, F-450, and F-550 Super Duty pickup trucks, and 2018-2019 Ford Explorer, 2019-2020 Expedition, and 2020 Escape vehicles equipped with driver and/or passenger\'s manual front seat back recliner mechanisms.  Also included are certain 2020 Ford Explorer and Lincoln Aviator vehicles equipped with rear outboard seats and manual seat back recliner mechanisms.  The recliner mechanisms may be missing the third pawl required for seat back strength, resulting in a loose seat back.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) numbers 202, "Head Restraints" and 207, "Seating Systems." ', u'Remedy': u"Ford will notify owners, and Ford and Lincoln dealers will inspect the seat structure and replace them, as necessary, free of charge.  The recall began October 21, 2019.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 19C07. ", u'ModelYear': u'2020', u'Model': u'ESCAPE', u'Make': u'FORD', u'ReportReceivedDate': u'/Date(1566964800000-0400)/', u'Manufacturer': u'Ford Motor Company'}]

[{u'NHTSACampaignNumber': u'19V784000', u'Conequence': u'In the event of a crash, incomplete body welding may provide inadequate protection to occupants, increasing the risk of an injury.', u'Notes': u'Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.', u'Component': u'STRUCTURE:BODY', u'Summary': u'Honda (American Honda Motor Co.) is recalling certain 2019-2020 Pilot and 2019 Passport vehicles.  The front frame left and right side upper members may not have been welded completely to the unibody.  As such, these vehicles may fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) numbers 208, "Occupant Crash Protection" and 219, "Windshield Zone Intrusion."', u'Remedy': u"Honda will notify owners, and dealers will inspect the vehicle for missing welds, free of charge.  If the vehicle is identified as missing welds, the dealer will offer to repurchase the vehicle or provide a similar replacement vehicle.  Owner notification will begin December 13, 2019. Owners may contact Honda customer service at 1-888-234-2138.  Honda's number for this recall is X6J.", u'ModelYear': u'2020', u'Model': u'PILOT', u'Make': u'HONDA', u'ReportReceivedDate': u'/Date(1572494400000-0400)/', u'Manufacturer': u'Honda (American Honda Motor Co.)'}]

[{u'NHTSACampaignNumber': u'19V720000', u'Conequence': u'A wheel detaching from the vehicle increases the risk of a crash.', u'Notes': u'Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.', u'Component': u'WHEELS:LUGS/NUTS/BOLTS', u'Summary': u'Hyundai Motor America (Hyundai) is recalling certain 2019 Ioniq Hybrid and 2020 Elantra vehicles.
